		  <td valign="top" width="60" align="center" class="borderClass" style="border: 0;"><div class="picSurround"><a href="/profile/Subpyro"><img src="http://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/userimages/thumbs/2350311_thumb.jpg" vspace="4" border="0"></a></div></td>
		  <td class="borderClass" style="border: 0;" valign="top">
		  <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><a href="/profile/Subpyro">Subpyro</a> <small><span style="font-weight: normal;"> | 04-24-14, 10:57 AM</span></small></div>
		  Guys and gals, allow me to tell you a short story. The events in it have actually happened in real life, so we could say it is based from a certain person's experience.<br />
<br />
The story takes place on a bus. A 24 year old boy accompanied by his father are one of the passengers. The boy has his eyes wide open, and is looking out of the window. He is really excited with everything he sees, and suddenly shouts out load: "Hey dad, look! The trees are running away from us!" The father smiles and says: "Yes, yes they are."<br />
<br />
Next to the two is a young couple, who quickly gets annoyed by the boy's screaming. The boy continues to look out of the window, all happy. Suddenly, he shouts: "Hey dad, it's amazing! The clouds are moving with us!" His father smiles again, saying: "Yes son, they sure are." At that point, the couple loses it, and tells the father to take his son to the doctor, as he is behaving far too weird for someone of his age.<br />
<br />
After they finish their complaint, the father smiles, and says: "Do excuse us, but we've just come back from the doctor. You see, my son was born blind, and after all these years, this is the first time in his life when he can see the world." After hearing those words, the couple couldn't find the words to apologize for what they've said.<br />
<br />
Just from hearing this, I get quite a vibe through my body. Although it doesn't sound really original, I think it would be worth expanding this situation in some sort of a story. I might just turn up writing something regarding it, with me being a lover of drama and all that. :)</td>
		</tr>
